		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You do it using the ceiling, being tall and jumping to the wall while ducking, hitting the wall while you're aligned to like a 16x16 section, making you unduck because it registers that you stepped on land, and when that happens your head gets stuck in the ceiling and it does the drag effect and brings you to the right.
<br />
<br />It's the same technique to do walljumps and crap.
<br />In my one hack, for some reason the minus world now points to some cloud level with a low thick ceiling and a bunch of crap in the way (so you have to preform the glitch even more).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
